\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
The ProMatrix Data Builder is a fully-active data dictionary that creates and manages application data.  ProMatrix automatically adds all of the system tables it includes in a project to the data dictionary.  You use the Data Builder to create new tables 
or to add existing tables to the project.  
\par \pard\plain \s47\sb180\sa180\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Note  }
You can access your application's data dictionary through the Data Builder option on the ProMatrix Tools menu or through the Data Manager option on the Admin menu of your application.  (The data dictionary is called the Data Manager on an application's me
nu because users of your applications will use the data dictionary more for managing data than for building it.)
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 The left side of the Data Builder lists the tables entered in the data dictionary.  The right side lists
 the fields in the selected table and shows the field types, dimensions and labels.  You use the check boxes at the bottom right to set properties for the selected field.
\par \pard\plain \s47\sb180\sa180\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\cs71\b Tip}
  Use the Data Builder to create all application tables, set table properties, set table relations and set field properties before you create application objects (i.e., screens, reports, queries and labels).  It's not only a good practice to do that, but 
if you do, ProMatrix will be able to automate much of the table setup required to create an object.
