 SECTION1:0005}}{\f103\fs24  }Purpose of the Data Builder
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
Generally speaking, the ProMatrix Data Builder provides an interface that lets you create an application's database and store the characteristics and properties of the database in FoxPro tables.   The FoxPro tables represent an automated data dictionary, 
or catalogue, that defines the application database.  Whenever your application needs to know the characteristics and properties of a database table or field, the information needed is readily available in the data dictionary tables.  
\par More specifically, the Data Builder and the data dictionary tables it creates and maintains provide the following functionality:
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber1}\'b7\tab }{\b Table Creation and Maintenance}
\par \tab You can use the Data Builder to:
\par \pard\plain \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }Create new application tables or import existing tables into an application's data dictionary.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Create and modify table indexes.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Identify a table's primary key.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Store important notes and comments about a table for later reference.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Change a table's structure.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Remove a table from an application's data dictionary.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Rename a table.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Reindex, pack and zap a table.
\par \pard \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 {\f1 \'b7\tab }Browse a table and enter table data.
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b Field Properties}
\par \tab You can use the Data Builder to set field properties to:
\par \pard\plain \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }Include a field in an application's audit trail.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Define validation rules for a field.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Force the contents of a field to be unique.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Store a default value for a field for new records added on screens.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Store a field label for screens and reports.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Store a field picture for screens and reports.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Define field security permissions. 
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Display your message when a field is edited.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Store important notes and comments about a field for later reference.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Display your field Help text when a field is edited and F3 pressed.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Display your error message when a field is edited and fails validation.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Prevent editing of a field unless a specified condition is true.
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\keepn\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b S{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber1}creens}
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Because the ProMatrix data dictionary is fully-active, it's used to run t
he screens you build in ProMatrix.  ProMatrix automatically adds FoxPro code to your screens that uses the data dictionary field properties to control the display and editing of table fields.  
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\keepn\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber2}\tab When you build an application screen to display and edit a table's data, ProMatrix uses the table's data dictionary entries to:
\par \pard\plain \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }Help you build the screen.
\par \tab ProMatrix presents you with a list of table fields.  You select the fields you want on the screen from the list.  ProMatrix automatically populates the screen with the fields you select and the field labels from the data dictionary.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Control how fields are displayed on the screen.
\par \tab The Picture field property controls a field's display.  The Permissions field property controls who can view and/or edit a field.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Control end-user data entry.  
\par \tab The Default field property puts a default value in a field when a user adds a new record.  The Integrity and Unique field properties define field validation rules and prevent erroneous data entries.  Other field properties 
provide messages and data entry field-level help.
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b Reports}
\par \tab 
When you create a report, ProMatrix presents you with a list of table fields.  You select the fields you want on the report from the list.  ProMatrix automatically populates the report with the fields you select and the field labels from the data diction
ary.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b D{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber2}ocumentation} 
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 The basic function of a data dictionary is to document an application's database.  The ProMatrix Data Builder and the data dictionary reports available through the Report Mana
ger provide full documentation of your application's database.  
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1\keepn \f5\fs20 
If you want to explore the ProMatrix data dictionary tables through FoxPro, the FoxPro table that stores information about an application's tables is called S<Prefix>DD1.DBF.  The FoxPro table that stores information about an application's fields is calle
d S<Prefix>DD2.DBF.
\par \pard\plain \s2\sb362\sa43\keepn \b\f5\fs36 {\f103 {\*\bkmkstart D2HTopicM47}\page }{\cs82\f103\fs16\up6 #{\footnote \pard\plain \s83 \b\f5\fs20 {\cs82\fs16\up6 #} Tables.10}}{\f103\fs24  }{\cs82\f103\fs16\up6 ${\footnote \pard\plain \s83 \b\f5\fs20 {
