Creating Tables
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Click the New push button on the Data Builder to create an application table.  ProMatrix displays the Save As dialog.
\par \pard\plain \s7\sb216\sa60 \b\f5\fs28 Table Name
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Enter the name of the table you are creating in the Save As dialog.  
\par Click the Create button after you enter the table name.  ProMatrix displays the Table Structure dialog.
\par \pard\plain \s7\sb216\sa60 \b\f5\fs28 Entering Table Fields
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 The Table Structure dialog is the same dialog used by FoxPro to define the fields in a table.  Enter your table's fields.  Press Enter or click OK after you've defined all the table fields.
\par If you have any questions about how to enter table fields in the Table Structure dialog, select FoxPro Help on the ProMatrix Help menu or refer to the FoxPro for Windows {\i User's Guide}.
