Adding Tables
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Click the Add push button on the Data Builder to add existing tables to an application's data dictionary.  ProMatrix displays the Add dialog.
\par The Add dialog lets you move among your computer's drives and directories to find the tables you want to add.  
\par \pard\plain \s65\sb120 \b\f5\fs20 To add existing tables to an application's data dictionary
\par \pard\plain \s17\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber5}1.\tab Use the Drive and Directory popups on the Add dialog to select the drive and directory t
hat contains the tables you want to add.  ProMatrix displays the table names in the directory in the Tables list on the left side of the Add dialog.
\par 2.\tab The Add dialog only displays files with a .DBF extension unless you select the All Files check box.  If you want to see all the files in a directory, select the All Files check box.
\par 3.\tab When you find a table to add, highlight it and click the Select button or double-click the table name.  The table's path and name will appear in the Selected Tables list on the right side of the Add dialog.
\par 4.\tab If you want to add all the tables in the directory, click the Select All button.  ProMatrix will display the path and names of all the tables in the directory in the Selected Tables list on the right side of the Add dialog.
\par 5.\tab If you want to remove a table from the Selected Tables list, highlight the table and click the Remove button or just double-click the table.  Click the Remove All button to remove all tables from the Selected Tables list.
\par 6.\tab When all the tables you w
ant to add are displayed on the Selected Tables list, click OK.  ProMatrix displays a dialog asking you to confirm that you want to add the tables to the data dictionary.  Click Yes to let ProMatrix Add the tables to the data dictionary.
\par 7.\tab I{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber5}f a table you want to add is outside the project's path, ProMatrix displays the Copy/Move Table dialog.
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 The Copy/Move Table dialog displays the table's path and name and gives you three choices:
\par \pard\plain \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber6}\'b7\tab }{\b C{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber6}opy}
\par \pard \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \tab Click the Copy button to copy the table along with index and memo files of the same name to the project's \\
DATA directory as shown in the Destination field on the dialog.  You can change the Destination field, but you would rarely want to.
\par \pard \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber7}\'b7\tab }{\b M{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber7}ove}
\par \pard \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \tab Click the Move button to move the table along with index and memo files of the same name to the project's \\
DATA directory as shown in the Destination field on the dialog.  You can change the Destination field, but you would rarely want to.
\par \pard \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber8}\'b7\tab }{\b L{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber8}eave}
\par \pard \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \tab Click the Leave button to leave the table where it is.  ProMatrix will store the p
ath to the file in the data dictionary.  You can see the path by highlighting the Table in the Tables list and clicking the Properties button.
