Creating Indexes
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Highlight a table on the Data Builder Tables list and click the Index push button to create or modify indexes for the table.  ProMatrix displays the Index dialog.
\par If a table has a structural compound index file, the indexes, or tags, in the file are displayed in the list box on the Index dialog.  Any files you add to the list are also displa
yed.  The Detail box on the lower half of the Index dialog displays the characteristics of the tag or file that is highlighted in the list box.
\par If the list box is blank, only the New, Add and Invert push buttons are enabled.
\par The push buttons on the Index dialog allow you to perform the following functions:
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber9}\'b7\tab }{\b New} - create a new index file or add a tag to an existing compound index file.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b Add} - add an existing index file to a table's index list.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b Modify} - modify the index highlighted in the list box.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b Reindex} - reindex the index highlighted in the list box.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b Delete }- delete the index highlighted in the list box.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b I{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber9}nvert} - automatically create a tag for every field in a table.  Creates a structural compound index file if one doesn't already exist.
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 The operation of the New, Add and Modify push buttons is described in the sections that follow.
