\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Click the New push button on the Index dialog to create a new index file or to add a tag to an existing compound index file.  ProMatrix displays
 the Create/Modify Index dialog.  You must be familiar with creating indexes in FoxPro to use the Index dialog.
\par When the Create/Modify Index dialog appears after clicking the New button, the File field contains the name of the compound index file highlighted on the Index dialog.  If the table's structural compound index file does not yet exist, ProMatrix will creat
e it if you complete the Create/Modify Index dialog and click OK.  
\par \pard\plain \s65\sb120 \b\f5\fs20 To create a structural compound index file for a table or to add a tag
\par \pard\plain \s17\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber11}1.\tab If the File field does not already contain the path and name of the table with a .CDX extension, make sure it does. 
\par 2.\tab C{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber11}lick the Expr button.  ProMatrix displays the FoxPro Expression builder. 
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Use the Expression Builder to construct the index expression.  If you need help using the Expression Builder, select FoxPro Help on the ProMatrix Help menu or refer to the FoxPro for Windows {\i 
User's Guide}.
\par \pard\plain \s75\li360\sa120\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Important}  If your index expression contains aliased fields, ProMatrix will offer to remove the aliases when you mo
ve from the Expr field.  Let ProMatrix remove the aliases.  It is highly recommended that you avoid using aliased fields when creating indexes.  Refer to the discussion of the Index command in the FoxPro {\i Language Reference} manual. 
\par \pard\plain \s76\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 3.\tab Enter  a tag name in the Tag field.  Tag names must begin with a letter or underscore and can consist of any combination of up to 10 letters, digits or underscores.
\par \pard\plain \s75\li360\sa120\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Tip  }Index tags with names that begin with an underscore (for example, _MyTag) are not shown on the Order and Lo
cate screen controls dialogs.  Beginning index tag names with an underscore is a convenient way of excluding index tags that you don't want to appear on the Order and Locate dialogs.  DELETED() tags are automatically excluded from display on the Order and
 Locate dialogs.
\par \pard\plain \s76\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 4.\tab Enter a description for the tag in the Desc field.  Enter a description that will make it easy for users of your application to identify the record order associated with the Tag.

\par 5.\tab Select the For button in the Options box if you want to make the index act as a filter for the table.  ProMatrix displays the FoxPro Expression builder.  Use the Expression builder to construct a logical filter expression.
\par 6.\tab Click the Descending radio button in the Options box if you want the index built in descending order.  Ascending order is the default.
\par 7.\tab Click the Unique check box to specify that only the first record encountered with a particular index key value is included in the index.
\par 8.\tab When the Create/Modify Index dialog is complete to your satisfaction, click OK.  ProMatrix builds the index and displays it in the list box on the Index dialog.
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 If you want to create an .IDX index file, start by entering the name of the file with an extension of .IDX in the File field.  Complete the Create/Modify Index dialog and click OK.
\par \pard\plain \s65\sb120 \b\f5\fs20 To create an .IDX index
\par \pard\plain \s17\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber12}1.\tab Enter the path and name of the index file with an .IDX extension in the File field.
\par 2.\tab Click the Expr button.  ProMatrix displays the Expression Builder.
\par \tab U{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber12}se the Expression Builder to construct the index e
xpression.  If your index expression contains aliased fields, ProMatrix will offer to remove the aliases when you move from the Expr field.  Let ProMatrix remove the aliases.
\par \pard\plain \s76\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 3.\tab Enter a description for the index in the Desc field.  Enter a description that will make it easy for users of your application to identify the record order associated with the index.

\par 4.\tab Select the For button in the Options box if you want to make the index act as a filter for the table.  ProMatrix displays the FoxPro Expression builder.  Use the Expression builder to construct a logical filter expression.
\par 5.\tab Click the Compact check box in the Options box if you don't want to create a compact .IDX file.  Compact is the default.
\par 6.\tab Click the Unique check box to specify that only the first record encountered with a particular index key value is included in the index.
\par 7.\tab When the Create/Modify Index dialog is complete to your satisfaction, click OK.  ProMatrix builds the index and displays it in the list box on the Index dialog.
