Index Information
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 ProMatrix stores information about a table's indexes in the Indexes memo field in the Tables data dictionary table (S<Prefix>DD1.DBF).  This stored indexes information is needed to implement the following f
eatures in ProMatrix:
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber13}\'b7\tab }{\b Complete Index Information:}
  When you access the Index dialog from the Data Builder or Data Manager screen, all information about indexes you previously added or created for a table is displayed.  
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b Index Description:}
  You can enter an index description for each index tag or IDX file you add or create for a table.  The Index dialog displays the index description.  You can create or modify an index description on the Create/Modify Index dialog.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b Reindex/Pack Tables Utility:}  ProMatr
ix adds a Reindex / Pack Tables Utility to the new applications it creates.  This utility allows users of your applications to recreate indexes if they become corrupt.  The utility uses the index information stored in the Index field to recreate indexes. 
 Users can also use the utility to pack tables to remove any records marked for deletion and to pack memo fields.  The {\i Reindex / Pack Tables Utility} section of the {\i Administrative Tools} chapter describes this utility in detail.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b O{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber13}rder Control Dialog:}  The O
rder push button screen control dialog displays the user-friendly index description to identify the indexes a user can select to determine the order of the records displayed on a screen.  {\i Appendix B - Screen Controls}
 describes the Order Control in detail.
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 When you exit the Index dialog, ProMatrix stores the following information in the Indexes field for each index listed on the dialog:
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber14}\'b7\tab }Index file name
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Tag name (if CDX)
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Description (up to 30 characters)
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Ascending/Descending code (A/D)
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Compact flag (T/F)
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Unique flag (T/F)
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Index expression
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }F{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber14}or expression
