}{\f103\fs24  }Setting Table Properties
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Highlight a table on the Data Builder Tables list and click the Properties push button to set up table properties.  ProMatrix displays the Properties dialog.
\par \pard\plain \s47\sb180\sa180\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Important}
  The most important item on the Properties dialog is the Primary Key popup.  For every table you add to an application, be sure to (1) create an index tag for the primary key field(s) and (2) select the primary key tag on the Property dialog's Prim
ary Key popup.  If you identify a table's primary key, ProMatrix will automatically prevent duplicate primary keys.
\par \pard\plain \s65\sb120 \b\f5\fs20 To set up table properties
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber15}\'b7\tab }{\b D{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber15}on't Swap}
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
Click the Don't Swap check box to prevent ProMatrix from closing the table if its work area is needed to open another table.  Only consider clicking the Don't Swap check box if your application will have more than 225 tables open at one time, which would 
be a rare event.
\par \pard\plain \s75\li360\sa120\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Note}  FoxPro for Windows has a limit of 225 open tables.  In the unlikely event that
 your application has 225 tables open at one time, the next time a table is opened ProMatrix closes the table that has been open the longest and opens the new table in its work area.  This table swapping feature was developed for earlier DOS versions of P
roMatrix that had to deal with a FoxPro limit of 25 open tables.  This feature probably has limited value in FoxPro for Windows, but since ProMatrix already had it, it was decided to keep it in case it might ever be of value to some developer.
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber16}\'b7\tab }{\b Path}
\par \tab Normally, there's nothing for you to enter in the Path field.  You only need to make an entry if ProMatrix cannot find the table file {\f1 \'be} see the following paragraphs.
\par \tab 
When ProMatrix displays the Properties dialog for a table, ProMatrix tries to find the table file using the path shown in the Path field.  If the Path field is blank, ProMatrix tries to find the table file in the current FoxPro path (that is, the project
 and ProMatrix directories).
\par \tab Most application tables reside in the FoxPro path.  If a table resides in the FoxPro path, the Path field on the Properties dialog is blank.  ProMatrix knows where to find the file when it's needed and doesn't need an entry in the Path field.
\par \tab I{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber16}f the table resides outside the current FoxPro path, the path field contains the path to the table.
\par \pard\plain \s75\li360\sa120\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Important}
  If the table file cannot be found when the Properties dialog is displayed, the Path field is editable and the Primary Key popup is blank.  In this event, you should enter the path to the table file in the Path field, or al
ternatively, move the table file to the location specified in the Path field or to the project's \\
DATA directory.  If the Path field contains an incorrect entry, and you don't know the correct path to the table file, you will have to blank out the Path field before you can leave the Properties screen.
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber17}\'b7\tab }{\b D{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber17}escription}
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Enter a brief description of the table; up to 30 characters.
\par The description you enter is displayed below the Data Builder Tables list when the table is highlighted.  
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber18}\'b7\tab }{\b P{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber18}rimary Key} 
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Click the Primary Key popup.  ProMatrix displays a list of the index tags in the table's structural compound index file.  Click the tag for the table's primary key field(s).  
\par If an index has not already been created for the table's primary key field(s), exit the Properties dialog and click the Index push button to create one.  Then, return to the Properties dialog and select the primary key tag on the Primary Key popup.
\par After you identify a table's primary key, ProMatrix automatically prevents duplicate primary keys i
n table records entered through the screens you build with ProMatrix.  ProMatrix also uses a table's primary key to automate the set up of Referential Integrity.
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber19}\'b7\tab }{\b C{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber19}omments} 
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
Enter any comments you want to record about the table in the Comments box at the bottom of the Properties dialog.  Enter as much text as you want.  The comments you enter can be used to provide users of your application important information about the tab
le.
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 When you've completed your entries, click OK to close the Properties dialog and save your entries.
