\par \pard\plain \s66\sa120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Highlight a table and click the Structure button to change the structure of the table.  ProMatrix displays the Table Structure dialog.
\par \pard\plain \s67\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 In the Table Structure dialog you can:
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sa60\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber20}\'b7\tab }Assign and change field names and attributes for the table.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Insert and delete fields in the table.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Change field sizes and types.
\par \pard \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 {\f1 \'b7\tab }A{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber20}dd and remove compound index tags.
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 If you need help using the Table Structure dialog, select FoxPro Help on the ProMatrix Help menu and search for "Table Structure dialog" or refer to your FoxPro for Windows {\i User's Guide}.
\par The Table Structure dialog is a FoxPro tool that changes the physical structure of a 
FoxPro table.  It does not update the ProMatrix data dictionary.  ProMatrix does that.  ProMatrix automatically updates the data dictionary for changes in table structure.  
\par However, if you (a) change the name of a field or (b) both insert at least one field and delete at least one other field, ProMatrix displays the Data Dictionary Update dialog.  
\par The Data Dictionary Update dialog lets you tell ProMatrix the original name of the field whose name you changed.  ProMatrix needs to know the original name so it can associate the field's existing data dictionary information with the new name.
\par \pard\plain \s66\sa120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
Also, inserting one field and deleting another field at the same time cannot be distinguished from a field name change.  Therefore, in this case, you have to tell ProMatrix that you're really just inserting a new field and not changing a field name.

