\par 3.\tab Repeat steps 1 and 2 for each field whose name you changed.
\par 4.\tab C{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber21}lick OK.  The new field names will appear in the Data Builder Fields list.
\par \pard\plain \s65\sb120 \b\f5\fs20 To identify a field insertion on the Data Dictionary Update dialog
\par \pard\plain \s76\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 1.\tab Highlight the inserted field name in the table fields list in the list box.
\par 2.\tab Click the "Map to" popup to display a list of the fields in the table's prior structure.  Double-click the "New Field" entry at the top of the popup list.  "New Field" now appears across from the inserted field name in the list box.
\par 3.\tab Repeat steps 1 and 2 for each field you inserted.
\par 4.\tab Click OK.  The inserted field names will appear in the Data Builder Fields list.
