\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Highlight a table and click the Remove button to remove the table from the data dictionary.  
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber22}\'b7\tab }ProMatrix displays a confirmation dialog.  If you
 click Yes to remove the table from the data dictionary, ProMatrix displays a dialog asking if you also want to delete the table file?  
\par \pard\plain \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }If you click No, ProMatrix removes the table from the data dictionary but does not delete the table file.  
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }I{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber22}f you click Yes, ProMatrix removes the table from the data dictionary and deletes the table file, the table's structural compound index file and the table's memo file, if any. 
