{\f103\fs24  }Audit Trail
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 You check the Audit Trail check box to include a field in the ProMatrix audit trail.
\par ProMatrix can automatically add an audit trail to the screens you build.  When a screen uses the ProMatrix audit trail, a record is made of data changes users enter on the screen.
\par The Audit Trail check box is a toggle that when checked for a field includes the field in the audit trail.  If for some reason, you do not want data changes made to a field to be included in the audit trail, uncheck the field's Audit Trail check box.

\par When you create a new table with the Data Builder or add a table to an application's data dictionary, the Audit Trail property is automatically turned on for every field in the table.  
