\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 When you click the Default check box, ProMatrix displays the Default Value dialog.  
\par \pard\plain \s66\sa120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 If a table field has a default value, enter that value in the Default field on the Default Value dialog.
\par \pard\plain \s67\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
The default value field is a character field.  Therefore, when you enter a default value for a non-character field, you should enter the value as it would appear in a character field.  For example, if the field is numeric with a default value of 12.34, en
ter the decimal point.  If the field is a date field, enter the default value in MM/DD/YY format, including the "/".  If it's a logical field,  enter T or F.
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 When a user adds a record to the table on a screen you build with ProMatrix, the default character value will be automatically converted to the correct type and entered into the field.
