\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Initially, the validation type is set to Not Null (explained below) and validation is turned off.
\par {\b Validation Type:}  You choose the validation type, or method, you want to use for a field on the Type popup.  
\par {\b Validation Option:}  You turn validation for a field on and off on the Option popup.   
\par The following is an overview of how to set up validation for a field.
\par \pard\plain \s65\sb120 \b\f5\fs20 To set up validation for a field - overview
\par \pard\plain \s17\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber35}1.\tab {\b T{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber35}ype:}  Click the validation Type popup.  The popup displays the following list of validation types, or methods:

\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 {\b Range
\par Set
\par Referential
\par Same As
\par Code
\par }\pard \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 {\b Not Null
\par }Click the validation type you want to use for the field.  ProMatrix changes the Integrity dialog to let you enter the information the validation type you selected needs.  Enter the validation information required.
\par \pard\plain \s76\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 2.\tab {\b Option:}  Click the validation Option popup.  The popup displays the following list of validation options:
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 {\b Off
\par On
\par On/Null
\par On/Override
\par }\pard \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 {\b On/Null/Override
\par }Click the validation option you want.  The validation options are used to:
\par \pard\plain \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber36}\'b7\tab }Turn validation for a field on and off.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Specify whether a null value, or no entry, in a field is acceptable.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }S{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber36}
pecify whether users can override a field's validation and force an invalid entry into the field.  If a user can override field validation, a dialog appears asking whether the user wants to override when the user enters invalid data into the field. 

\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 The validation options have the following meanings:
\par \pard\plain \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber37}\'b7\tab }{\b Off} 
\par \tab No validation performed on the field.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b On} 
\par \pard\plain \s73\fi-360\li1080\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx1080 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }Validation performed on the field.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }A null value, or no entry, {\ul not acceptable} unless a null value is a valid entry under the validation rules entered for the field.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }User {\ul cannot override} validation.
\par \pard\plain \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b  On/Null}
\par \pard\plain \s73\fi-360\li1080\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx1080 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }Validation performed on the field.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }A null value, or no entry, {\ul is acceptable}.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }User {\ul cannot override} validation.
\par \pard\plain \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b On/Override}
\par \pard\plain \s73\fi-360\li1080\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx1080 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }Validation performed on the field.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }A null value, or no entry, {\ul not acceptable} unless a null value is a valid entry under the validation rules entered for the field.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }User {\ul can override} validation and force an invalid entry.
\par \pard\plain \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b On/Null/Override}
\par \pard\plain \s73\fi-360\li1080\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx1080 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }Validation performed on the field.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }A null value, or no entry, {\ul is acceptable}.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }U{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber37}ser {\ul can override} validation and force an invalid entry..
