Compound foreign keys
\par \pard\plain \s47\sb60\sa120\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Shortcut}
  If a foreign key includes more than one field, set up referential integrity for the first field in the key.  Then, use Same As validation for the other fields to validate them just like the first.
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Changing one of the fields in a compound foreign key on a data entry screen can cause a temporarily invalid foreign key combination.  The combination is temporarily invalid
 if it will become valid when the remaining fields in the key are changed.  Handle this problem by using a validation option for the foreign key that allows an override.  Then, if a temporarily invalid foreign key combination occurs, it can be overridden 
if the other foreign key fields will be changed so that a valid combination exists.
\par If you press F2 while editing a compound foreign key field and select an entry in the F2 window, ProMatrix replaces all the fields in the compound foreign key with your selection.
