\par You can control whether an F2 Help picklist is editable by field and user.
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber52}\'b7\tab }{\b Field:  }
You can choose which fields have editable F2 Help picklists.  You make the F2 Help picklist editable for a field by checking the Edit check box on the Integrity dialog for a field that uses the Referential Integrity Type.  If you choose not to make the F2
 Help picklist editable for a field, the edit buttons will not appear when the picklist is displayed for the field.
\par \tab The users of your application can also turn this edit feature on and off for a field if you include the Data Manager in your application.  
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b User:  }
The system administrator of your application can choose which users have the right to edit the F2 Help picklists.  If the system administrator assigns a user the F3 Edit right on the User Data screen, that user will also have the right to edit the F2 Help
 picklists.  If a user does not have the right to edit the F2 Help picklists, the edit buttons will not appear when the picklist is displayed for a field.
\par \tab T{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber52}he system administrator must turn System Access Security on to make the F3 Edit right operable.  If System Access Security is not on, all users have the right to edit F2 Help picklists that are made editable.  See the {
\i System Access Security - User Data} section of the {\i Security }chapter for an explanation of System Access Security and the F3 Edit right.
\par \pard\plain \s65\sb120 \b\f5\fs20 To make F2 Help picklists editable for a user
\par \pard\plain \s17\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber53}1.\tab Select the User option on the Security menu.  You reach the Security menu from the application's Admin menu.  ProMatrix displays the User Data screen.

\par 2.\tab Find the User to whom you want to give the right to edit the F2 Help picklists.
\par 3.\tab C{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber53}lick the Edit button on the User Data screen.  Enter "Y" in the F3 Edit field in the Authorization box.  Click the OK button to save your entry.
