rence table record is displayed and the user can enter all the fields in the record.
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
When a user clicks the Delete button, a confirmation alert dialog is displayed.  If the user proceeds with the delete, the selected record will be deleted subject to the Referential Integrity rules set up in the data dictionary between the Reference table
 and other application tables.
\par \pard\plain \s6\sb120 \b\f5 Caution
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 The ability to edit the F2 Help picklist is intended to provide a quick way for selected users to Add, Delete and Edit records in a s
imple lookup table while performing routine data entry on another table.  It is not intended to replace the need for a full data entry screen for the lookup table.  It is also not intended to be used for data entry into a complex table that is not merely 
a lookup table.
\par Not all field properties are operable when adding or editing records through an editable F2 Help picklist.  Specifically, the following field properties are not operable:
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber54}\'b7\tab }{\b Integrity, or field validation, property.}  If a table that is used b
y a field as a Reference table for Referential validation requires field validation when its records are entered, do not make the F2 Help picklist that displays fields from the Reference table editable.  This kind of Reference table needs its own data ent
ry screen with full field validation.  Generally, you should only make the F2 Help picklist editable for simple lookup tables that consist of code and label fields.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b U{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber54}nique, Permissions, Message, Help, Error and When properties.}  None of these field properties are operable when adding or editing records through an F2 Help picklist.
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 The following field properties are operable while adding or editing records through an F2 Help picklist:
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber55}\'b7\tab }{\b Entity Integrity.}  ProMatrix prevents a duplicate or null entry into the primary key of the Reference table.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b Referential Integrity.}  If a Reference table record is deleted or a primary key updated, Referential Integrity is enforced as established in the data dictionary between the Reference table and other application tables.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b Audit Trail property.}  The audit trail is maintained for additions, deletions and edits.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b Default property.}  Default values will appear when a record is added through an editable F2 Help picklist.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b P{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber55}icture property.}
  The picture property is partially operable.  If a field's picture property forces entry of the field in uppercase, the field will be forced to uppercase when it is entered through an editable F2 Help picklist.  No other part of a field's picture propert
y entry is operable.
\par \pard\plain \s4\sb216\sa14\keepn \b\f5 {\f103 \page }{\cs82\f103\fs16\up6 #{\footnote \pard\plain \s83 \b\f5\fs20 {\cs82\fs16\up6 #} F2HelpPicklistNotAvailableforBrowseScreens.61}}{\f103  }{\cs82\f103\fs16\up6 ${\footnote \pard\plain \s83 \b\f5\fs20 {
