}}{\f103\fs24  }{\cs82\f103\fs16\up6 K{\footnote \pard\plain \s83 \b\f5\fs20 {\cs82\fs16\up6 K} Cleanup Code}}{\f103\fs24  }{\cs82\f103\fs16\up6 +{\footnote \pard\plain \s83 \b\f5\fs20 {\cs82\fs16\up6 +} SECTION1:0270}}{\f103\fs24  }Cleanup Code
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Click the Cleanup check box on the upper right corner of  the Integrity dialog and ProMatrix displays the Cleanup Code dialog.  You can enter FoxPro code in this dialog to be run:
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber56}\'b7\tab }If a field passes the validation rules defined by the Integrity dialog and the Unique property, or
\par \pard \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sa240\sl281\slmult1\tx360 {\f1 \'b7\tab }I{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber56}f the validation Option is set to off for the field.
\par \pard\plain \s67\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 You can use the Cleanup Code dialog to:
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber57}\'b7\tab }Apply additional validation rules to a field.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }U{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber57}pdate or calculate other fields using the new field value {\f1 \'be} this is sometimes called a relational edit.  
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Entering cleanup code is much like entering Code validation.  The same rules apply and the same memory variables are available.  At the time your code is run, the memory variable {\b\f11 slCurValue}
 contains the field value.  Your code can set the logical memory variable {\b\f11 sllRetVal}
 to false (F) if the code is validating the field and the field fails validation.  Your code can return the error message to display if the field fails validation by assigning the message as a character string to the character memory variable {\b\f11 
slcRetMess}.
\par \pard\plain \s65\sb120 \b\f5\fs20 To create Cleanup Code for a field
\par \pard\plain \s17\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber58}1.\tab Click the Cleanup check box on the Integrity dialog.  ProMatrix displays the Cleanup Code dialog
\par 2.\tab E{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber58}nter your code in the text box on the Cleanup Code dialog.  You can use the following memory variables in your code if you need them:
\par \trowd \trgaph108\trleft-108 \cellx2070\cellx7290 \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sa60\sl281\slmult1\keepn\intbl \f5\fs20 {\b Memory Variable}\cell {\b Purpose\cell }\pard\plain \intbl \f5\fs20 \row \trowd \trgaph108\trleft-108 \cellx2070\cellx7290 \pard\plain 
\s16\sb60\sl281\slmult1\intbl \f5\fs20 {\b\f11 slCurValue\cell }Contains the field value.  Use this value in your code.\cell \pard\plain \intbl \f5\fs20 \row \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1\intbl \f5\fs20 {\b\f11 sllRetVal\cell }\pard 
\s16\sb60\sl281\slmult1\intbl Returns the result of a validation.  If validation fails, set {\b\f11 SllRetval} to F.  If validation passes, set to T.\cell \pard\plain \intbl \f5\fs20 \row \trowd \trgaph108\trleft-108 \cellx2070\cellx7290 \pard\plain 
\s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1\intbl \f5\fs20 {\b\f11 slcRetMess\cell }\pard \s16\sb60\sa60\sl281\slmult1\intbl Returns an error message to display if validation fails.  Assign a character string to {\b\f11 slcRetMess}.  For example:
\par \pard \s16\sb120\sa60\sl281\slmult1\intbl {\b\f11\fs16 slcRetMess = "Field must have at least 4 characters"}\cell \pard\plain \intbl \f5\fs20 \row \pard\plain \s17\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 3.\tab Click OK.
\par \pard\plain \s6\sb120 \b\f5 Find Program
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
You can call a program to handle cleanup code instead of entering code in the text box.  Put your call to the program in the text box.  You can click the Find Program button to find the name of the program.  When you find the name of the program, ProMatri
x replaces any code you've entered in the text box with the name of the program followed by "()".
\par \pard\plain \s47\sb180\sa180\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Warning } If you've entered code in the text box, don't access the Find Program button.  If you do, you could inadvertently replace y
our code with a program file name.
\par \pard\plain \s57\sb180\sa20 \b\f5\cf2 See Also:
\par \pard\plain \s88\sa60\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20\uldb Using Cleanup Code Validation with Override Option{\v UsingCleanupCodeValidationwithOverrideOption.63}
