Data Manager
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 You can access an application's data dictionary through the Data Builder option on the ProMatrix Tools menu or through the Data Manager option on the application's Admin menu.  
\par Data Builder and Data Manager are just different names for the same dialog.  The dialog is called the Data Manager in an application because users of an application use the data dictionary more for managing d
ata than for building it.  The dialog gets its window title from the menu option prompt that runs it.  Therefore, you can change the Data Manager window title just by changing its menu prompt.
\par Data dictionary functions that require program compilation are disabled on an application's Data Manager.  Most ProMatrix applications are distributed as .EXE's.   Functions that require program compilation won't run in an .EXE.  Therefore, such functions
 are disabled to prevent runtime errors.
