Building Reports, Labels & Queries
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
The primary purpose of database applications is to allow users to process and retrieve information.  In FoxPro users can retrieve data in the form of reports and labels built with the FoxPro Report Writer or as queries created with FoxPro's Re
lational Query By Example (RQBE).
\par With ProMatrix you can build reports and labels that run:
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sa60\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber63}\'b7\tab }From ProMatrix's unique Report Manager,  
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }From menu options, or
\par \pard \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 {\f1 \'b7\tab }A{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber63}s called objects. 
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 ProMatrix automatically puts the Report Manager in every application you build.  Users of your applications can run the reports you create and create their own reports through the Report Manager.
\par With ProMatrix you can build FoxPro RQBE queries as menu objects or called objects.  Because FoxPro does not support RQBE in .EXE files, end users cannot modify an RQBE query in an application unless you distribute it as an .APP file.
\par \pard\plain \s47\sb180\sa180\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Reports Means Labels}
