\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 If you want to remove a report from an application's Report Manager list, highlight the report and click the Remove button.  
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber64}\'b7\tab }
ProMatrix displays a dialog requiring you to confirm your intent to remove the report.  If you click Yes, ProMatrix displays another dialog asking if you want to delete the report file.  
\par \pard\plain \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }If you click Yes, ProMatrix will delete the report file.  
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }I{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber64}f you click No, ProMatrix will remove the report from the application's Report Manager list, but it will not delete the report file.  You can then later r
estore the report to the Report Manager list through the Add button.
