\s83 \b\f5\fs20 {\cs82\fs16\up6 +} SECTION2:0030}}{\f103\fs24  }Creating Reports for the Report Manager
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 While you are developing an application, you have three ways of creating reports for the application's Report Manager.
\par \pard\plain \s69\fi-360\li360\sb120\sa60\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \b\f42\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber65}\'b7\tab }R{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber65}eports Run from Menu Options
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
When you use the Object Builder to create a report to run from a menu option, ProMatrix automatically adds it to the Report Manager.  Users can then run the report from the menu option or the Report Manager.  
\par If you don't want the report to appear in the Report Manager, you can remove it without deleting the report file.
\par \pard\plain \s69\fi-360\li360\sb120\sa60\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \b\f42\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber66}\'b7\tab }T{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber66}ools Menu Report Builder
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
You can select the Report Builder on the Tools menu to create reports for an application.  The Report Builder works and looks just like the application's Report Manager but it's in ProMatrix.  The reports you create with the Report Builder become part of 
the application you are creating.
\par \pard\plain \s75\li360\sa120\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Tip}  While you're building your application, you'll find the Report Builder to be the most convenient way to creat
e reports for the Report Manager.
\par \pard\plain \s69\fi-360\li360\sb120\sa60\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \b\f42\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber67}\'b7\tab }A{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber67}pplication's Report Manager
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
You can use an application's Report Manager to create reports.  You can run the application by clicking the Object Builder's Run Application button or by selecting Run Application on the Tools menu Test popup.  Then, select the Report Manager on the appli
cation's Reports menu to build reports.
\par \pard\plain \s66\sa120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 If you create a report with the Report Builder or Report Manager, you first click the New button to add the report's name to the Report Manager list.  T
hen, you click the Open button to use the Report Editor dialog to construct the report.
\par \pard\plain \s65\sb120 \b\f5\fs20 To create a report with the Report Builder or Report Manager 
\par \pard\plain \s76\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 1.\tab {\b New Report/Label Dialog:}
  Click the New button on the Report Builder or Report Manager.  ProMatrix displays the New Report/Label dialog.  Enter an eight character file name for the report.  Choose OK.
\par 2.\tab {\b Report Editor:}  Click the Open button on the Report Builder/Manager.  ProMatrix displays the Report Editor dialog.  Enter a title for the report in the report Title field.{\b  }
\par 3.\tab {\b Table Setup:}  Click the Table Setup button on the Report Editor and set up the tables for the report.  Be sure to enter the main report table first so that it automatically becomes the report's Active Table.  
\par 4.\tab {\b Build Object Dialog:  }Click the Edit button.  ProMatrix displays the Build Object dialog.  
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 The Build Object dialog lets you choose one of the following three options:
\par \pard\plain \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber68}\'b7\tab }{\b Blank:}  Open the FoxPro Report Writer with a blank report.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b Copy:}  Make the report you are creating a copy of an existing report.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b Q{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber68}uick:}  Open the ProMatrix Quick Fields dialog to select the fields you want ProMatrix to put on the report.  This is the option you normally select.
\par \pard\plain \s76\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 5.\tab {\b Quick Fields Dialog:  }Select the Quick radio button on the Build Object dialog and click the OK button.  ProMatrix displays the Quick Fields dialog.
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 {\b Select Fields}:  The Quick Fields dialog displays the fields in the report's active table in the Fields list box.  Select the Fields you want to include in your report.  Highlight a fiel
d and double-click it or click the Select button.  Selected fields appear in the Selected Fields list box.  When you click OK, ProMatrix adds the fields you select and the fields' labels and pictures from the application's data dictionary to the report.

\par {\b Select Options:}  You can choose to have ProMatrix add the selected fields to the report vertically or horizontally.  You can also choose to have ProMatrix add aliases to the field names.  The defaults are Horizontal and Add Alias.
\par \pard\plain \s76\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 6.\tab {\b FoxPro Report Writer:}  Click OK on the Quick Fields dialog.  ProMatrix creates your report and displays it in the FoxPro Report Writer. 
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
ProMatrix lays out the field labels from the application's data dictionary as headings and positions the fields under them or to the right of them depending upon whether you selected a horizontal or vertical layout.
\par If you need help with the FoxPro Report Writer, see your FoxPro for Windows {\i User's Guide}. 
\par At this point, you need to complete your report.
\par \pard\plain \s76\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 7.\tab {\b Leaving the Report Writer:}  When you're 
ready to leave the FoxPro Report Writer, double-click the close box.  Save your changes.  ProMatrix returns to the Report Editor.  The next time you click Edit on the Report Editor, you'll go right to the FoxPro Report Writer.
\par \pard\plain \s75\li360\sa120\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Don't Save the Environment}
  Don't save the report environment when using the FoxPro Report Writer.  ProMatrix uses it's own table setup routine for reports.  Using the FoxPro Save Environment will conflict with the ProMatrix table setup routine.
\par \pard\plain \s76\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 8.\tab {\b Options Dialog:}  Click the Options button on the Report Editor.  ProMatrix displays the Options dialog.
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
The Options dialog allows you to customize the ProMatrix Report Setup dialog for each report.  The Report Setup dialog is a front-end for reports that gives users extensive control over the presentation and contents of a report.
\par Check  the top box on the Options dialog to include the Report Setup dialog with the report.  Check the bottom three check boxes to enable the Order, For and While options on the Report Setup dialog.  Click OK.
\par \pard\plain \s76\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 9.\tab {\b Test:}
  Your report should now be ready to test.  Click the Run button on the Report Editor to test the report.  ProMatrix displays the Report Setup dialog.  Click the Preview button to view your report.
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 If you need to modify the report after testing, click the Edit button on the Report Editor to open the FoxPro Report Writer and make your modifications.
