\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 The ProMatrix Report Editor organizes the development of any functions you need to create to build a report.
\par \pard\plain \s66\sa120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 The Report Editor contains a list box in which you can enter the names of the functions a report calls.  When you select a function name on the list, you access the FoxPro Text Editor for that function.
\par \pard\plain \s67\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 The User Functions control buttons do the following:
