  Click the Blank radio button on the Build Object dialog to create the function from scratch.  ProMatrix inserts the same code it puts into any program.  You may need to remove the table opening and closing routines.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b Copy:}  Click the Copy radio button to create the function by copying an existing function.
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 \tab You can also double-click an entry in the User Functions list to edit it.
