\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 ProMatrix automatically adds the reports you create for your applications to the FoxPro Project Manager but marks them as Excluded.  ProMatrix puts reports in the Project Manager for your refere
nce.  It marks them as Excluded so that end users can modify them.  
\par If you want to prevent users from modifying a report, open the Project Manager for your application from the ProMatrix Tools menu.  Highlight the report in the Project Manager and click the Include option on the Project menu.  When you build your applicat
ion, the report will be included in the .APP or .EXE file.  Then, don't  distribute the report files separately.
\par \pard\plain \s47\sa120\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Tip}  ProMatrix includes a Users Report and a Passwords Report in the applic
ations it creates.  When you prepare an application for distribution, mark these two reports in the Project Manager to be Included in the .APP or .EXE file.  Don't distribute these report files separately.  This prevents unauthorized users from accessing 
these reports by adding them to the Report Manager. 
