\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 You can use your existing FoxPro DOS reports in a ProMatrix application, but you must transport them to FoxPro for Windows before you can edit them in ProMatrix.  See your FoxPro for Windows {\i 
Developer's Guide} to learn how to transport FoxPro DOS files to FoxPro for Windows. 
\par \pard\plain \s4\sb216\sa14\keepn \b\f5 {\f103 \page }{\cs82\f103\fs16\up6 #{\footnote \pard\plain \s83 \b\f5\fs20 {\cs82\fs16\up6 #} RunningReportsin.EXE.s.83}}{\f103  }{\cs82\f103\fs16\up6 ${\footnote \pard\plain \s83 \b\f5\fs20 {\cs82\fs16\up6 $}
