 }Running Reports in .EXE's
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
The FoxPro library file that currently supports .EXE's has a bug that affects FoxPro reports.  The bug changes the Fill Color for report text objects to black when a report is run from an .EXE.  The report text objects look fine when run from an .APP file
.  Changing a text object's Fill Color to white while running an .EXE does not solve this problem.  You must change a text object's Mode to Transparent.
\par \pard\plain \s47\sb120\sa120\sl281\slmult1\keepn\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Tip}  If your application will be packaged as an .EXE, change the Mode of report text objects to Transparent as you build a report.
