\f103\fs24  }System Access Security
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
System Access Security prevents unwanted entry into ProMatrix and the applications you build with ProMatrix.  System Access Security requires users to enter a valid ID and password before they can access an application.  
\par \pard\plain \s47\sb180\sa180\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Note}  This section describes System Access Security in terms of how you set it up for ProMatrix
.  However, the descriptions of how System Access Security works and how you set it up apply equally to the applications you build with ProMatrix.  
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
When ProMatrix is installed, System Access Security is turned off.  You must enter users and their passwords on the User Data screen before System Access Security can be turned on through the Admin Tools screen.
\par \pard\plain \s47\sb180\sa180\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Tip}  Distribute your applications with System Access Security turned off.
