\par \pard\plain \s66\sa120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 When you run ProMatrix with System Access Security on, ProMatrix displays the User Log-On dialog. 
\par \pard\plain \s67\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Enter your ID and password.  If you press the escape key, you will exit ProMatrix.  You are allowed three attempts to enter a valid password.  Upon the third invalid entry, you exit ProMatrix.  
\par When a valid password is entered, ProMatrix checks to see if it is time for you to enter a new p
assword.  It is time to enter a new password if the current date is equal to or greater than the date calculated by adding the Password Period entry in your User record to the date you last changed your password.  
\par You may enter a new password at any time by entering the Change Character after your password.  Initially, the Change Character is a question mark, "?".  The Change Character is described in the {\i Security Setup} section later in this chapter.  
\par If a new password is to be entered, ProMatrix displays the New Password Dialog.
\par \pard\plain \s3\sb340\keep\keepn \b\f5\fs28 {\f103 \page }{\cs82\f103\fs16\up6 #{\footnote \pard\plain \s83 \b\f5\fs20 {\cs82\fs16\up6 #} NewPassword.86}}{\f103\fs24  }{\cs82\f103\fs16\up6 ${\footnote \pard\plain \s83 \b\f5\fs20 {\cs82\fs16\up6 $}
