\cs82\fs16\up6 +} SECTION3:0040}}{\f103\fs24  }Assigning Permissions
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 You can assign Menu Security permissions  to users in two ways:
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber96}\'b7\tab }{\b Individual Permissions:}
  You can assign permissions to a user on an individual basis through the Menu Permissions button on the Users Data screen.  
\par \pard\plain \s55\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 1.\tab Display the user's record on the Users Data screen.
\par 2.\tab Click the Menu Permissions push button on the Users Data screen.  ProMatrix displays the Menu Permissions dialog.  
\par 3.\tab See the{\i  Menu Permissions Dialog}  subsection below to learn how to assign individual permissions using that dialog.
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b Group Permissions:}  You can assign a user the permissions that have already been assigned to a group of users. 
\par \pard\plain \s55\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 4.\tab Display the user's record on the Users Data screen.
\par 5.\tab Enter the code of the menu permission group to which the user should belong in the Menu Group field.  With the cursor on the Menu Group field, press F2 to see a list of the menu permission groups that you have set up.
\par 6.\tab S{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber96}ee the {\i Menu Permission Groups Screen} and {\i Menu Permissions Dialog}  to learn how to set up menu permission groups and assign group permissions.
\par \pard\plain \s57\sb180\sa20 \b\f5\cf2 See Also:
