\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Field Security allows the system supervisor to prevent certain users from viewing or making changes to fields on screens.  
\par \pard\plain \s47\sb180\sa180\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Note}
  This section describes Field Security in terms of how you set it up for ProMatrix.  However, the descriptions of how Field Security works and how you set it up apply equally to the applications you build with ProMatrix.  
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 You can prevent data from specified fields from being displayed on a sc
reen for selected users (No Display).  You can also prevent specified fields from being edited by selected users (Display Only).  No Display and Display Only field security is applied to groups of users, not individual users.  
\par Because Field Security is assigned to individual users (through group assignments), Field Security is disabled if System Access Security is turned off.
