Field Permissions Dialog
\par \pard\plain \s66\sa120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 You use the Field Permissions dialog to assign field permissions (restrictions) to field permission groups.  You reach this dialog from the Field Properties Permissions check box on the Data Manager screen.

\par \pard\plain \s67\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 {\cs71 The fields and control buttons on the Field Permissions dialog are described below.
\par }\pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber124}\'b7\tab }{\cs71\b G{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber124}roups List}
\par \pard \s62\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 
The group codes and descriptions of all field permission groups are listed in the Groups list.  To the right of each group code and description is the permission (restriction) status.  A blank means there is no restriction for the group.  A "d" means the 
Display Only restriction has been selected for this group.  An "n" means the No Display restriction has been selected for this group.
\par \pard \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber125}\'b7\tab }{\cs71\b R{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber125}estrictions}
\par \pard \s62\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 
Click on the None radio button to signify that users in the highlighted group can view and edit this field.  Click on the Display Only radio button to signify that users in the highlighted group can view the data in this field but not make changes to it. 
 Click on the No Display radio button to signify that users in the highlighted group cannot view or make changes to the data in this field.
\par \pard \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber126}\'b7\tab }{\cs71\b O{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber126}K}
\par \pard\plain \s70\li360\sb120\sa100\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 When you click OK, a number is stored in the field's data d
