\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
Display Only field security does not require any special code insertion.  It is handled automatically in the field When routine that is called from the code that is already inserted into every field's When clause to handle a screen's edit mode.
\par No Display field security is handled through the use of GENSCRNX directives th
at are inserted into every field's Comment clause.  These directives are automatically inserted when you exit the FoxPro Screen Builder and return to the Edit Object dialog.  Then, when a screen program is run, the directives cause the ProMatrix field sec
urity routine to be run for each field.  Those fields for which the user has been restricted from viewing are not included in the screen.
