Security Builder
\par \pard\plain \s66\sa120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 Before you package your application for distribution, you must run the ProMatrix Security Builder to prepare the application's Menu and Control Security.  You access the Security Builder from the Tools menu.  

\par \pard\plain \s67\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 When you click the Build push button, ProMatrix does the following:
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber127}\'b7\tab }
ProMatrix enters the titles of all screen sets and browses in your application into the S<Prefix>CDC table.  The title of a screen set is the title of the first screen in the screen set that is not a control panel or ID screen.
\par \tab The titles of screen sets and browses are used on the Control Permissions dialog to display the list of screens and browses in your application.  It is from this list that control permissions are assigned.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }P{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber127}roMatrix enters information about all of the menu options on all of the menus in your application into the S<Prefix>SMNU table.
\par \pard \s62\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 The information about the menu options in your application is used on the Menu Permissions dialog to display the list of menu options.  It is from this list that menu permissions are assigned.
