\par \pard\plain \s66\sa120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 You can reach the Activity screen from the PM-Admin menu or from the Admin menu of an application.  The Activity screen lets you view each user's activity records.
\par \pard\plain \s67\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 You use the information on the Activity screen if questions arise regarding a user's activity in an application.
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 When the Activ
ity screen first appears, it shows information for the last activity that occurred for the current user.  The activity records are shown in descending order of the time and date the activity occurred.  
\par \pard \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1\keepn You can:
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber129}\'b7\tab }{\b Order:}  Change the order to ascending through the Order button on the Activity screen.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b All Users:}  If you've implemented System Access Security in your application, you can view activity for all users who have run the application by clicking the All Users radio button in the Filter box.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b All Apps:}  If the application is sharing its activity file with another application, you can view activity for all applications by clicking the All Apps radio button in the Filter box.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }{\b S{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber129}creen Controls:}  You cannot edit or add activity records but you can delete them.  You should delete the activity records before you package your application. 
