\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 The ProMatrix audit trail is a system management tool that ProMatrix builds into the screens you create.   The audit trail tracks a user's:
\par \pard\plain \s62\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber130}\'b7\tab }Field data changes.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Record additions.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }R{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber130}ecord deletions.
\par \pard\plain \s66\sa120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 A field's audit trail field property must be on before the field's data changes are included in the audit trial.  The default audit trail field property is on.  See the {\i Fields - Audit Trail}
 section of the {\i Building Data }chapter.
\par You can reach the Audit Trail screen from the PM-Admin menu or from the Admin menu of an application.  The Audit Trail screen lets you view each user's audit trail records.
\par \pard\plain \s67\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 You use the information on the Audit Trail screen to monitor data changes in an application.
\par \pard\plain \s16\sb120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
When the Audit Trail screen first appears, it shows information for the last data change made by the current user.  The audit trail records are shown in descending order of the time and date the activity occurred.  
