\cs82\fs16\up6 +} SECTION4:0060}}{\f103\fs24  }Reindex / Pack Tables Utility
\par \pard\plain \s66\sa120\sl281\slmult1 \f5\fs20 
When you create a new application, ProMatrix includes a Reindex / Pack Tables utility on the application's File menu.  This utility allows users of your applications to recreate indexes if they become corrupt.  Users can also use the utility to pack table
s to remove any records marked for deletion and to pack memo fields.  ProMatrix includes this same utility on its File menu.
\par \pard\plain \s65\sb120 \b\f5\fs20 To use the Reindex / Pack Tables Utility
\par \pard\plain \s17\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber133}1.\tab Click either the Reindex
 or the Pack radio button.  If you select Pack, FoxPro will also reindex the tables you select, but it will not recreate the indexes from scratch the way ProMatrix does. 
\par 2.\tab 
The Tables list on the left side of the dialog shows all the tables in the application, including system tables.  You select the Tables you want to reindex or pack.  When you select a table, the Selected Tables list on the right side of the dialog disp
lays the table's name.
\par 3.\tab You can select:
\par \pard\plain \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }A table individually by highlighting it in the Tables list and double-clicking it or clicking the Select button.  
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }All tables by clicking the All>> button.  
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }All application tables by clicking the All Application button.  ProMatrix identifies application tables as the tables whose names begin with a character other than "S".
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }All system tables by clicking the All System button.  ProMatrix identifies system tables as the tables whose names begin with "S".
\par \pard\plain \s17\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 4.\tab You can remove tables from the Selected Tables list by:
\par \pard\plain \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }Highlighting an individual table and double-clicking it or clicking the Remove button.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Clicking the <<All button.  ProMatrix will remove all tables from the Selected Tables list.
\par \pard\plain \s17\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 5.\tab When you have selected the tables you want, click OK and the reindex or pack operation begins.
\par 6.\tab If you are reindexing, the utility performs the following steps:
\par \pard\plain \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }All tables that the user performing the reindex has open are closed.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Then, for each selected table:
\par \pard\plain \s73\fi-360\li1080\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx1080 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }The table's indexes as stored in the data dictionary Indexes field are deleted.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }T{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber133}he table is opened exclusively.  
\par \pard\plain \s75\li360\sa120\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Note}
  If an application is running in a multi-user environment and another user has a table open that is to be reindexed, the table cannot be opened exclusively.  An alert dialog is displayed that informs the user performing the reindexing that the table will
 not be reindexed.  When the user clicks OK on the alert dialog, the reindexing proceeds for other tables.  Accordingly, when a user performs reindexing in a multi-user environment, it's a good idea to send a message to othe
r users to exit the application so that all selected tables can be reindexed. 
\par \pard\plain \s73\fi-360\li1080\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx1080 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber134}\'b7\tab }The table's indexes are rebuilt using the index information stored for the table in the application's data dictionary.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }T{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber134}he table is closed.
\par \pard\plain \s75\li360\sa120\sl281\slmult1\brdrt\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \brdrb\brdrs\brdrw15\brsp20 \f5\fs20 {\b Reindex Button on Index Dialog}
  If you include the Data Manager in your application, users can reindex tables one-at-a-time through the Reindex button on the Index dialog.
\par \pard\plain \s76\fi-360\li360\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx360 \f5\fs20 7.\tab If you are packing, the utility performs the following steps:
\par \pard\plain \s64\fi-360\li720\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx720 \f5\fs20 {\f1 {\*\bkmkstart D2HBulletNumber135}\'b7\tab }All tables that the user performing the pack has open are closed.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }Then, for each selected table:
\par \pard\plain \s73\fi-360\li1080\sb120\sl281\slmult1\tx1080 \f5\fs20 {\f1 \'b7\tab }The table is opened exclusively.  (The {\b Note} shown above about reindexing in a multi-user environment applies to packing as well.)
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }All indexes for the table are opened so that they are updated as the table is packed.
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }The table is packed and reindexed by FoxPro. 
\par {\f1 \'b7\tab }T{\*\bkmkend D2HBulletNumber135}he table is closed.
